<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>MariaDB Knowledge Base Comments for: Index Hints: How to Force Query Plans</title><link>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/index-hints-how-to-force-query-plans/+comments/feed/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://mariadb.com/kb/en/index-hints-how-to-force-query-plans/+comments/feed/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 09 Mar 2023 22:08:03 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>STRAIGHT_JOIN behaves as an INNER JOIN</title><link>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/index-hints-how-to-force-query-plans/+comments/2887</link><description>&lt;p&gt;STRAIGHT_JOIN behaves as an INNER JOIN, afaict. (The MySQL and Maria manuals seem not to mention this.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So adding it to a query, as described in this article, might change the meaning of the query and not just the plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Iow, take care! Using STRAIGHT_JOIN might change your query from an implicit LEFT JOIN to an implicit INNER JOIN. &lt;/p&gt;
